install helm?

curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/main/scripts/get-helm-3 | bash

helm version

This downloads the latest Helm v3 version and installs it.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

HELM? 

Helm is a package manager for Kubernetes, similar to how apt works for Ubuntu or yum for CentOS.

Instead of writing huge YAML files, Helm lets you package them into charts (reusable templates).

You can install, upgrade, and manage Kubernetes applications easily using these charts.

---------------------------------------------------------

ðŸ”¹ Why do we use Helm?

**Simplifies Kubernetes deployment**s

One helm install can deploy dozens of YAMLs (Deployments, Services, Ingress, ConfigMaps, etc.).

**Reusable & shareable charts**

Community charts exist for popular tools (NGINX, Prometheus, Grafana, ArgoCD, etc.).

You donâ€™t need to reinvent the wheel â€” just customize values.

**Configuration via values.yaml**

Instead of editing manifests directly, you just override settings in a simple values file.

**Versioned & Rollbacks**

Helm tracks versions of releases.

If something breaks, you can roll back with one command.

**Easier upgrades**

Upgrading an app is as simple as helm upgrade with new values.

-----------------------------------------------------------

ðŸ”¹ Advantages of Helm

âœ… Speeds up deployment (no need to write 100s of lines of YAML).
âœ… Makes apps portable and reproducible across environments.
âœ… Supports templating & parameterization.
âœ… Huge ecosystem of official and community charts.
âœ… Rollbacks built-in.

---------------------------------------------------------------

helm upgrade --install <name> . --> expects Chart.yaml in current directory
helm status <name>
helm rollback <name> --> 1 revision back
helm uninstall <name>

helm repo add <URL>
helm update
helm install name <location


helm install nginx . --> . represents current directory
helm upgrade nginx . --> updates to latest version
helm list --> list all helm apps running

helm status nginx 


